8 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
9 An Act relating to Oklahoma Agricultural Extension;
prohibiting the required centralization and
10 redirection of local revenues; authorizing local
funds be held by local financial institutions;
11 prohibiting comingling with state or federal funds;
providing for codification; and declaring an
12 emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3419.1 of Title 70, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. No entity or division under the control of the Board of
20 Regents for the Oklahoma Agricultural and Mechanical Colleges,
21 including but not limited to, the Oklahoma Agricultural Extension
22 Division, shall directly, or as a condition of receiving Oklahoma
23 Agricultural Extension Division services or access to Oklahoma
24
Req. No. 16458 Page 1

1 Agri cultural Experiment Station programming, require funding
2 generated at the local level be:
3 1. Centralized at the division or station; or
4 2. Directed or expended outside the county in which the funding
5 was generated.
6 B. Local level funds may be held in accounts at local financial
7 institutions, provided such accounts shall not comingle local funds
8 with state or federal funds.
9 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
10 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
11 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
12 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
